This approach leverages a frequency map (or dictionary in Python) to count how many numbers fall into each parity category (000 for even and 111 for odd). After counting, we use the combination formula, similar to Approach 1. While this method is functionally similar to counting even and odd numbers directly, it introduces the concept of using hash maps to solve frequency-based problems, which is a useful technique in many algorithms.

**Time Complexity:**

O(N)O(N)O(N) per test case.

